---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';

const breadcrumbItems = [
  { label: 'Home', href: '/' },
  { label: 'Terms' },
];

const lastUpdated = '13 April 2026';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Use | Peninsula Insider"
  description="Terms of use for Peninsula Insider, including acceptable use, intellectual property, and automated extraction restrictions."
  section="home"
>
  <Breadcrumbs items={breadcrumbItems} />

  <section class="legal">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="legal__header">
        <p class="label label--accent">Terms</p>
        <h1 class="legal__title">Terms of Use</h1>
        <p class="legal__updated">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
      </div>

      <div class="legal__body prose">
        <p>Peninsula Insider is an independent editorial publication. By accessing or using this site, you agree to these terms. If you do not agree, do not use the site.</p>

        <h2>Editorial purpose</h2>
        <p>This site exists to provide editorially curated information, recommendations, and destination guidance about the Mornington Peninsula. Content is provided for general information and planning use. It is not a substitute for checking live venue, event, booking, weather, safety, or transport information directly with the relevant operator or authority.</p>

        <h2>Accuracy and change</h2>
        <p>We work to keep content current, but venues change hours, events move, bookings sell out, and conditions shift. We do not guarantee that every page is complete, current, or error-free at every moment. You should verify time-sensitive details before relying on them.</p>

        <h2>Intellectual property</h2>
        <p>Unless otherwise stated, all editorial copy, site structure, curation logic, original graphics, branding, and compiled guides on Peninsula Insider are protected by copyright and other intellectual property rights. You may read, share, and link to the site for personal, editorial, or non-commercial reference. You may not republish, systematically reproduce, or commercially exploit material from the site without written permission.</p>

        <h2>Automated access and extraction</h2>
        <p>You may not use bots, scrapers, crawlers, scripts, bulk collection tools, or other automated methods to extract, reproduce, mirror, republish, train on, or commercially reuse substantial portions of Peninsula Insider content without express written permission.</p>
        <p>This restriction includes, but is not limited to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>mass downloading or copying of articles, listings, place guides, itineraries, or event data</li>
          <li>building derivative destination or directory products from our editorial corpus</li>
          <li>using Peninsula Insider content or structured extracts to train or improve commercial AI models without permission</li>
          <li>circumventing rate limits, bot controls, or technical protections</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Reasonable search-engine indexing, citation, and linking are allowed where consistent with our robots policy and normal web use.</p>

        <h2>External links and bookings</h2>
        <p>We link to third-party venues, booking providers, operators, and external sites. We do not control those sites and are not responsible for their content, availability, pricing, policies, or behaviour. If you choose to book or transact with a third party, that relationship is between you and them.</p>

        <h2>No professional advice</h2>
        <p>Nothing on this site is legal, medical, financial, or safety advice. Where activities involve surf, coastal conditions, bushland, alcohol, children, or travel logistics, exercise your own judgement and check the relevant official guidance.</p>

        <h2>Acceptable use</h2>
        <p>You agree not to use this site in a way that:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>harms or attempts to harm the platform, its infrastructure, or other users</li>
          <li>interferes with site availability or performance</li>
          <li>misrepresents Peninsula Insider content as your own</li>
          <li>uses the site for unlawful, deceptive, or abusive purposes</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Future products and gated features</h2>
        <p>Peninsula Insider may introduce new products, accounts, memberships, concierge tools, newsletters, saved itineraries, or app-like experiences over time. Additional terms may apply to those services when launched.</p>

        <h2>Changes to these terms</h2>
        <p>We may update these terms from time to time. If we make material changes, we will update the date at the top of this page. Continued use of the site after changes take effect means you accept the revised terms.</p>

        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>For permissions, licensing, or terms enquiries, contact <a href="mailto:hello@peninsulainsider.com.au">hello@peninsulainsider.com.au</a>.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
